org.alternativevision.gpx.extensions

Interface IExtensionParser

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DummyExtensionParser

    public interface IExtensionParser
    This interface defines extension parsers methods.

    All custom extension parser must implement this interface.

    Any custom parser must be added to GPXParser as an extension parser before parsing a gpx file, or writing a GPX to a file. This is done by calling addExtensionParser() method of GPXParser

    GPXParser parseGPX method calls several methods from the registered extension parsers added at different steps of processing:

    • parseGPXExtension() for parsing <extensions> of a <gpx> node
    • parseTrackExtension() for parsing <extensions> of a <trk> node
    • parseRouteExtension() for parsing <extensions> of a <rte> node
    • parseWaypointExtension() for parsing <extensions> of a <wpt> node

    GPXParser writeGPX method also calls several methods from the registered extensions parsers at different steps of writing data:

    • writeGPXExtensionData() when writing the <extensions> from the GPX
    • writeTrackExtensionData() when writing the <extensions> from the Track
    • writeRouteExtensionData() when writing the <extensions> from the Route
    • writeWaypointExtensionData() when writing the <extensions> from the Waypoint
